// ===========================================================================
// OVERLAY OVERRIDE: "skillsDir"
//
// Copies a folder of EXTRA skills into the repo, on top of the skills the core
// package ships. Use it for org- or domain-specific skills you don't want in
// the public package (internal runbooks, house conventions, product playbooks).
//
// "skillsDir" is a path to a folder that contains one sub-folder per skill, each
// with a SKILL.md (same layout as the core skills). It may be:
//   - relative to THIS overlay file (e.g. "./acme-skills"), or
//   - an absolute path.
//
// Expected layout of the referenced folder:
//   acme-skills/
//     acme-release-runbook/SKILL.md
//     acme-incident-response/SKILL.md
//
// These skills are rendered per platform like the core skills: Claude gets
// .claude/skills/, Codex gets playbook files + an AGENTS.md index entry, and
// Copilot gets .github/instructions/*.instructions.md.
//
// Merge rule: each skill file is copied only if it doesn't already exist
// (unless init is run with --force).
//
// Apply with:  samwise init --overlay examples/overlay-skills.json
//
// The path below is FICTIONAL - point it at your own skills folder.
// ===========================================================================
{
  "skillsDir": "./acme-skills"
}
